a plural noun by adding s to a singular noun car car s.";i:46;s:80:"Words that end in -ch x s or s-like sounds take -es for the plural kiss kiss es.";i:47;s:61:"English Etymology chair person after chairman and chairwoman.";i:48;s:123:"Noun chairperson plural chairpersons or chairpeople A chairman or chairwoman someone who presides over a meeting board etc.";i:49;s:71:"She was the chairperson of the board and she presided over the meeting.";i:50;s:21:"Plural form of chair.";i:51;s:71:"Noun 2 0 Third-person singular simple present indicative form of chair.";i:52;s:93:"Verb 1 0 Advertisement Chairs Sentence Examples He sat in one of the chairs visibly relaxing.";i:53;s:88:"She sat in one of the chairs and slid down in it until her head rested against the back.";i:54;s:132:"A plural noun indicates that there is more than one of that noun while a singular noun indicates that there is just one of the noun.";i:55;s:91:"Most plural forms are created by simply adding an -s or es to the end of the singular word.";i:56;s:58:"For example theres one dog singular but three dogs plural.";i:57;s:60:"However English has both regular and irregular plural nouns.";i:58;s:94:"Door bats mean boot over dogs pens desk it Singular means only one plural means more than one.";i:59;s:78:"Not all words are nouns hat cat mat rugs shoes big under ball on floor chairs.";i:60;s:37:"A The chairs covers are all the same.";i:61;s:35:"B The chairs cover is all the same.";i:62;s:69:"Both sentences belong to standard English but they differ in meaning.";i:63;s:62:"A plural distributive subject all plural collective predicate.";i:64;s:55:"B singular distributive subject all singular predicate.";i:65;s:26:"The girl sat on the chair.";i:66;s:73:"This is a singular sentence because there is only one girl and one chair.";i:67;s:25:"Plural means two or more.";i:68;s:28:"The girls sat on the chairs.";i:69;s:92:"This is a plural sentence because there are two or more girls sitting on two or more chairs.";i:70;s:76:"You need to be very careful when changing sentences into plural or singular.";i:71;s:55:"Definitions and Meaning of chair in English chair noun.";i:72;s:35:"The position of professor Synonyms.";i:73;s:69:"Professorship Example - he was awarded an endowed chair in economics.";i:74;s:116:"A seat for one person with a support for the back Example - he put his coat over the back of the chair and sat down.";i:75;s:70:"A particular seat in an orchestra Example - he is second chair violin.";}}